<br>
This is where I kind of disagree with you Nyca.  Yes, Sev is just one mob, but I believe the policy suggestions being discussed here are not mob specific and could overall increase the rotation system's efficiency.<br>
<br>
You absolutely positively have to change something to urge the ongoing and forward progression of the rotation system.  Without movement, you have no rotation.<br>
<br>
The bottom line, as I see it, is that rotation is a race of the current top of the list rotation guild ...and all guilds not yet on that rotation.  All fine and dandy ...the problem is, there is no penalty for losing the race over and over again.  This is something that, I think, can be taken advantage of.  What does the top of the list rotation guild have to lose?  Nothing, absolutely nothing at all.<br>
<br>
Discussing the possibility of implementing a solution like Rogg's would go a long way in easing this tension.  At the very least, the suggestion should be allowed to attain proposal status and discussed in representative committee (those far more knowledgeable than I), rather than be out and out vetoed.  Of course, I do not know the process for doing that ...I likely wouldn't have the ability ...but that, in itself, should not be the death of a good idea.<br>
<br>
I realize that this forum holds no real power over the server, but I argue that the representative committee holds enough respect to give it some authority in these matters. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=arianrhodsidhe>Arianrhod Sidhe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>S4H - GL</span><br>  Posts: 158<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(12/3/02 12:17:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=887.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Rotation Rules?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>You absolutely positively have to change something to urge the ongoing and forward progression of the rotation system. Without movement, you have no rotation.<br>
